  "original_title": "\u0b87.\u0baa\u0bcb.\u0b9a \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1 : \u0baf\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Stone pelting on EC bus: Youth arrested",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "The police have said that a person has been arrested for the crime of pelting stones at a bus owned by Sri Lanka Transport Board yesterday (11) in Vavuniya Puliankulam area.",
        "The young woman who had diverted the EPO bus from Jaffna to Vavuniya at Puliyankulam area was angry because the bus did not stop.",
        "In this case, the enraged girl threw stones at the bus. Due to this, the glass of the bus is stuck.",
        "On the basis of the complaint filed by the bus driver, the police arrested a 28-year-old woman in connection with the incident and after further investigations, the preliminary proceedings are being conducted in the Magistrate's Court today."
      ],
